<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-15004] Anti-compaction briefly corrupts sstable state for reads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15004</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since we use multiple sstable rewriters in anticompaction, the first call to prepareToCommit will remove the original sstables from the tracker view before the other rewriters add their sstables. This creates a brief window where reads can miss data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13213220">CASSANDRA-15004</key>
            <summary>Anti-compaction briefly corrupts sstable state for reads</summary>
